{
  "stem": "14060.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Something was-- But it didn't happen to us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, it was just a story, like a bad dream or a film you see, and then you leave the film, you shut-- and you go on home and you try to forget about it.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But obviously, you couldn't forget about it, because it kept on recurring.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the next really impressive memory I have was not that Shabbat, the week after.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The shul, the Orthodox shul, which I still have a picture of it, even though it became completely-- it was sort of neglected, they used it as a horses' stables during-- after the deportation and it's gone into neglect-- would show the size of the building.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But there were a few hundred families who sort of lived in town, of which maybe the maximum attendance would have been about 200 family heads, maybe their parents or children and so on.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But on that Shabbat, which was a week and a day after Hitler marched into Austria, the shul was full to capacity, which I never seen before or after.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There wasn't a millimeter space.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "People stood practically outside.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "These were all Austrian Jewish refugees who managed to come immediately across the border, had relations in our town, and all tried to take refuge, which in fact they managed to do, because maybe some of them had some birthright of Hungarian birthright or something.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Anyway, obviously-- And the one person who I can never get out of my mind-- face-- there was a thin, medium-built man.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I was told he was a rabbi of Kobersdorf.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That also one of the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The man was blue-and-black, beaten in his face, on his arm, his hands, swollen.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I never forget.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
